HEADWORD: Sepiment
<hw>Sep"i*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sepimentum</ets>, <ets>saepimentum</ets>, from <ets>sepire</ets>,
<ets>saepire</ets>, to hedge in.]</ety> <def>Something that separates; a
